Musicbee has a really good, and extremely flexible, method for auto-renaming/arranging your media based on the metadata tags stored within them.

The great thing is not only does it support standard tags/metadata, but also custom ones (though limited to a maximum of 16-20 if i remember correctly).

The downside is MusicBee is only available on Windows.

How can I create something that does the same thing but is:
- Fully Multiplatform, supported on windows and macOS (maybe even Linux)
- Automatically starst on login (or preferably starts as a service) and silently/continuously monitors specific folders for files in the background (constant monitoring preferred over regular/periodic monitoring). However any file open in another app should not be moved/edited by this application until the file is no longer in use. In such cases the application should 'remember' the file to be processed, and proceed returning to the remembered file once it is no longer in use (this is to prevent files from unintentionally being corrupted)
- can run when a computer boots (preventing having to manually be started), this must be configurable by the user of course. It would also be good to be able to be run as a service on platforms that support it, therefore not needing a specific user to login.
- not resource heavy
- support for all popular audio & video formats/containers, including: mpg, mp3, mp4, m4a, m4v, ac3, eac3, ac4, flac, ALAC, mkv, mka, avi, divx, ogg, hevc etc)
- support for differentiating audio characteristics including: lossy vs lossless, multichannel formats (Dolby digital, Dolby digital plus etc), Spatial Audio (Dolby Vision, Reality Audio 360 etc). For use with sorting files. (perhaps MediaInfo could be used?)
- support for character replacement (for instances where a metadata tag contains a character that isn’t supported in file paths/filenames)
- Ability to differentiate between 'Media Types' (ie Music, Music Video, TV Show, Movie/Film, Podcast, Radio Show etc)
- Support for thing like IF AND OR conditions for sorting/auto-arranging criteria with nesting as well
- Any third-party libraries/components need to be able to be packaged with the application for easier install
- The ability to connect to, monitor and auto-arrange media on CloudServices (OneDrive, OneDrive For Business/SharePoint, Google Drive, Mega.nz, iCloud, Dropbox would) would also be useful. though this is a future feature. While planning for this can be done as part of the projectc outline and code structure, please lets add this much later as a future feature

Media files will likely be tagged with tools like MusicBrainz Picard and MP3tag, but the added ability to edit/manage metadata would also be a useful (future) feature.

The ability to define auto/arranging criteria both by typing them but also with a UI. Method for defining auto arranging rules can use commands in a similar way to MusicBee (see here: https://musicbee.fandom.com/wiki/Functions and https://musicbee.fandom.com/wiki/Templates for info), but with the ability to use a potentially endless number of standard and/or custom tags.

some folder may even contain 'companion files', like SRT, LRC subtitles files, or even disk image/ISO files (ISO, NRG), cover art (JPG, PNG), Animated cover arty (cover.mp4 etc). IF all MUSIC files are moved from one folder to another, their companion files must also be moved.

We're aiming for flexible, wide feature/capabilities but still easy to use and user friendly/configurable.



Please can we adjust the order of the final two project goals. Metadata editing should be done before cloud ssync monitoring.

Additionally, as a further feature, Metadata Editing should (later, including integration with MusicBrainz, Apple Music, Spotify - for similar look/features to OneTagger, Tidal, Amazon Music, Shazam - for further track identification etc, Apple TV (Tv/Movies), TheTVDB (TV Shows), TheMovieDB (Movies), IMDB (MOvies) As a additional feature, support for looking up and downloading(/saving as MP4) of Animated cover art (square and vertical/portrait) should also be supported.

So, after UI & CLI the scope will be as follows, in this order

1) manual Metadata editing
1.1) Music Metadata lookup - Media lookup should also be able to store the direct URL to the song from for each service in dedicated custom tags
1.1a) MusicBrainz
1.1b) Apple Music
1.1c) Spotify
1.1d) Tidal
1.1e) Amazon Music
1.1f) Shazam (for music identification/fingerprinting, ability to store Shazam ID/string reppresentation of fingerprint in dedicated custom tag)
1.1d) AcousticBrainz
1.2) TV/Movie Meta Data lookup - Media lookup should also be able to store the direct URL to the song from for each service in dedicated custom tags
1.2a) Apple TV
1.2b) iTunes Store
1.2c) TheTVDB
1.2d) TheMovieDB
1.2e) IMDB
1.2f) EIDR (Lookup and embed EIDR ID)
2) Cloud Sync/Monitoring

Note, App must support tags with multiple values, as suitable for each format/container. Standard format/containers should be used wherever possible, with custom metadata tags following this rule wherever possible. We want to ensure that all files remain playable on all supported/players devices, even if some cannot utilise the custom metadata tags.

The app should also fully support dark/light UI modes, either specifically defined, or based on system config. 

 API keys for third-party systems should be stored securely in GitHub repo (or the app itself if a 'universal' API Keys can be used and are within the third-party service ToS). We should perhaps also allow the end user to insert their own APIs to use over any 'centrally'/'universal' provided API keys? In cases where its against the ToS of a service to (or advised against) use a single API Key for all end-users, then the central should not be used by end users in the packaged version, and is only for use by developer. Perhaps include an easy to use 'toggle' for each API key on whether or not it should be included in the packaging.

Please also include the ability for GitHub to auto-create packages for each platform.

(one i forgot. Mac support should ONLY be for Apple Silicon. Windows support should be for x64 and ARM. Linux should support x86/x64 and ARM where applicable)

Can we also add one final milestone (at the very end), in this order
* Ability to configure to export info of your media liibrary to an external database. Supporting (in this order, with a new milestone/release after each is implemented): MySQL, MariaDB, SQL Server, SQLite, PostgreSQL. - this can then be used to create a highly flexible, searchable intranet/web-hosted index of library. 
* (FINALLY) Ability to choose whether or not to also export/copy of the media files to the web server and include a reference link to the file in the aformentioned external database (though this needs to be highly secure, with use access config to avoid piracy concerns). This should also have support for multiple formats of the song media item (FLAC Lossless, ALAC Lossless, lossy (m4a, mp3 etc))

Can the project plan and outline be updated again accordingly before we get started, as a 'sense-check'?

Any code should be produced with full DETAILED Annotations and comments to assisst with understanding what each line/block of code does, help with debugging, learning and future expansion. Code blocks not use shorted annotation, but rather full code to assist further with code reading and understanding.

Code and project progress is to be uploaded and managed in a GitHub Repo. The Repo may include code from previous/earlier iterations, but we're happy to replace all of this (apart from product name "MeedyaManager" and logo/branding). Any files no longer needed should be deleted.

To assist with future development and maintenance, a modularised development architecture is preferred.

PLease produce ALL code with user-readable code formatting (linebrakes, indentation etc), and include DETAILED comments/annotations for code (if possible every line of code) to assist with learning, future code maintenance and code understanding.

Please also include comments in the code including license/copyright and author info.
License should be in line with GAMDL source project and the other components/libraries used. We do not want this project to conflict with any of those.
Copyright year in source code (comments) should be auatomated, and start in 2025, endind in the <current year> with the current year being added/automated in all code without manual intervention.
Copyright should be held with MWBM Partners Ltd.


